00:38:23.230 --> 00:38:26.330
have to, using your right
hand, rotate in a

00:38:26.330 --> 00:38:27.820
counterclockwise sense.

00:38:27.820 --> 00:38:31.650
And therefore, the streamers
go out again in

00:38:31.650 --> 00:38:33.950
the opposite direction.

00:38:33.950 --> 00:38:37.440
Same for 4 sub 1.

00:38:37.440 --> 00:38:40.390
There, every edge of the
square is enclosed.

00:38:40.390 --> 00:38:44.360
If you look at how you have to
rotate to get from the one on

00:38:44.360 --> 00:38:47.510
top to the one immediately below
using your right hand,

00:38:47.510 --> 00:38:50.830
again, you have to rotate
in a clockwise sense.

00:38:50.830 --> 00:38:56.770
And therefore, the edges that
are elongated trail out in the

00:38:56.770 --> 00:38:58.780
opposite direction.

00:38:58.780 --> 00:39:03.770
And finally, drawn in a decent
fashion are 6 sub 1, 6 sub 5,

00:39:03.770 --> 00:39:06.240
which are spirals in
the opposite sense.

00:39:06.240 --> 00:39:11.160
6 sub 2, 6 sub 4, pairs of
things at each level.

00:39:11.160 --> 00:39:13.340
And the level is 1/3
of the translation.

00:39:13.340 --> 00:39:17.700
6 sub 3, triangles of objects at
intervals that are equal to

00:39:17.700 --> 00:39:26.920
1/2 of T, 3/6 of T. OK,
does that answer?

00:39:26.920 --> 00:39:29.650
That is really a convention
of some higher order.

00:39:29.650 --> 00:39:31.630
But nevertheless, it is
a convention and it is

00:39:31.630 --> 00:39:32.880
consistent.

00:39:35.290 --> 00:39:37.481
Other questions about
screw axes?

00:39:37.481 --> 00:39:37.968
Yeah?

00:39:37.968 --> 00:39:40.403
AUDIENCE: So in nature, is there
a difference between the

00:39:40.403 --> 00:39:41.864
right handed screw
[INAUDIBLE]?

00:39:45.290 --> 00:39:48.940
PROFESSOR: That's like asking
is there something like a

00:39:48.940 --> 00:39:51.660
Coriolis effect in crystals.

00:39:51.660 --> 00:39:54.000
You know the Coriolis effect
that if you're in the southern

00:39:54.000 --> 00:39:57.640
hemisphere, the water gurgles
down the drain one direction.

00:39:57.640 --> 00:39:58.870
If you're in the northern
hemisphere,

00:39:58.870 --> 00:40:00.120
the opposite direction?

00:40:03.960 --> 00:40:09.080
There was actually a very
famous scientist,

00:40:09.080 --> 00:40:10.320
what was his name?

00:40:10.320 --> 00:40:12.370
I think it was Serret.

00:40:12.370 --> 00:40:14.200
Serret, so famous I can't
think of his name.

00:40:14.200 --> 00:40:22.660
I remembers his name, Serret
He developed a very famous

00:40:22.660 --> 00:40:26.150
theorem in kinetics, and that
was thermal migration,

00:40:26.150 --> 00:40:29.250
migration driven not by a
chemical potential gradient

00:40:29.250 --> 00:40:32.120
but by a temperature gradient.

00:40:32.120 --> 00:40:34.820
And it's very difficult
to measure.

00:40:34.820 --> 00:40:37.620
And only recently have people
been testing that theory and

00:40:37.620 --> 00:40:39.710
making measurements.

00:40:39.710 --> 00:40:41.590
He asked this very
same question.

00:40:41.590 --> 00:40:46.900
And he said, I think it was
potassium chlorate that he

00:40:46.900 --> 00:40:50.670
looked at which has no mirror
plane or inversion in it.

00:40:50.670 --> 00:40:53.690
So it occurs in left handed
and right handed forms.

00:40:53.690 --> 00:40:57.250
He asked, is there something
like a Coriolis effect that

00:40:57.250 --> 00:41:00.660
would give you more right
handed crystals in the

00:41:00.660 --> 00:41:03.130
northern hemisphere and more
left handed crystals in the

00:41:03.130 --> 00:41:04.260
southern hemisphere?

00:41:04.260 --> 00:41:06.350
So what he'd do, he drew
a lot of crystals.

00:41:06.350 --> 00:41:07.560
And he started counting.

00:41:07.560 --> 00:41:09.320
And he counted, and he
counted, and counted.

00:41:09.320 --> 00:41:10.990
And he couldn't tell if there
